article.description: Jaylen Franklin had 19 points and Jaren Lewis added 14 while grabbing 10 rebounds as Abilene Christian knocked off the Southland Conference leaders Sam Houston State 71-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Franklin has 19 as Abilene Christian tops league-leader SHSU
article.linkText: Franklin has 19 as Abilene Christian tops league-leader SHSU
article.story: ABILENE, Texas -- Jaylen Franklin had 19 points and Jaren Lewis added 14 while grabbing 10 rebounds as Abilene Christian knocked off the Southland Conference leaders Sam Houston State 71-64 on Saturday. Franklin made 6 of 11 field goal attempts. Lewis was 8 of 8 from the free throw line as the Wildcats made 27 of 32 free throws. SHSU was 14-of-26. Hayden Farquhar added 13 points for Abilene Christian (10-12, 4-7) which has won two straight. The Wildcats had a 27-19 lead at the half. SHSU tied it at 40 at the 10:30 mark. Lewis responded with a jumper and three straight free throws to start an 11-0 Wildcats run. SHSU's Paul Baxter drilled a 3 to close to 65-61 with 37 seconds left. ACU's Isaiah Tripp made four free throws and Franklin had a layup to seal the win. Dakarai Henderson had 20 points for SHSU (17-7, 8-3) which had previously won eight straight.
